A 34-year-old man was shot and killed in a hail of bullets on Thursday night, 11 February, in Barberton in Mpumalanga. Police spokesman Brigadier Leonard Hlathi said the man, who was a well-known taxi boss, was in his parked taxi when the incident happened. He said as he was trying to get off, the suspect, who was also known to the police, fired shots, killing him instantly. Hlathi said the motive for the killing was still unknown. On the day of the incident, a war broke out between Pienaar and Barberton taxi drivers. Those from Barberton went further and blocked roads. A murder case had been opened, and police were appealing to anyone with information to assist them.